		 Domain-based Message Authentication,
		        Reporting and Conformance (DMARC)

section.t:
The Receiver of this message (a list subscriber, in this case) can conclude that the following are true, based on the remaining valid signatures:
"example.com" authorized "ietf.example" to sign mail on its behalf;
"ietf.example" signed the altered content, thus taking some responsibility for it;
This chain of handling satisfies the need for the Author domain to have signed the message; the original message may have been modified or replaced, but such action was explicitly approved by the Author domain.
